    "Table 5 provides links to these benchmarks.",
    "Advanced techniques in graph processing6.1 Dynamic transfer learning Transfer learning employs the knowledge of a model trained on one task (called the source task) to facilitate the learning of another distinct but related task (called the target task).",
    "The core idea is to share specific knowledge between the source and the target task.",
    "This concept is based on the observation that various tasks frequently share underlying features or patterns.",
    "Consequently, insights from one task can potentially benefit another [101,102]."
